{
  "name": "design-a-robust-fix-for-stale-20260413-0518",
  "idea": "Design a robust fix for stale pinnedShotGroup.trackId in the video editor. Context: pinnedShotGroup.trackId is denormalized state that says which track a group's clips live on, but it can become stale when clips move across tracks. We just fixed the most critical data-loss bug (clips silently deleted on drag) in multi-drag-utils.ts, but 26 of 38 usages of group.trackId are vulnerable. The audit found 11 HIGH RISK (data loss) and 15 MEDIUM RISK (silent failures) call sites across usePinnedShotGroups.ts, useTimelineTrackManagement.ts, useSwitchToFinalVideo.ts, shot-group-commands.ts, and others. Two approaches: (1) defensive helper that resolves actual trackId from clip positions at each call site, or (2) ensure trackId is updated atomically whenever clips move. Need a plan that's robust but not over-engineered \u2014 this is a video editor timeline, not a distributed system.",
